From 5b7c485fe3628c0b2381c6e03596882b73cb81b7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Joshua-Eisenhart <40147598+Joshua-Eisenhart@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 15:33:34 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 32/35] feat(claim-gate): generic manifest-driven CR-sim engine
 obligation kind
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

cr_sim_packet_v0: a CR sim onboards as a host-executed Lev workload by
adding a data manifest (packet.json) in a host-owned carrier dir, not a
new TS envelope builder per sim. loadCrSimPacketManifest is fail-closed:
simId regex (no traversal), host-owned carrier resolution only, pinned
sha256 verified against script bytes AT LOAD, executed negative control
required per lane (env allowlisted LEV_CR_*), result artifacts confined
to results/, timeout capped. New engineMode manifest_lanes_required:
requiredLanes must exactly match manifest lanes at execution.
simPacketId is validated and folded into the normalized obligation
(binds into obligationHash). Pilot A (cr_fingerprint_floor_v1) migrated:
its builder now delegates to the generic path via a packet.json carrying
the identical hash pins; behavior and kind string unchanged. Coratchet
builder untouched this slice.

Also: widen EvidenceRefCarrier.actualResult to unknown with runtime
narrowing — the seam-1 patch (b01e0b6fe) passed vitest but broke tsc
(TS2345 vs ProofObligation.actualResult).

Verified: typecheck clean, orchestration 828/828 (8 new tests),
independent live run of buildRealCrSimPacketEnvelope spawned real
julia+jax with sealed receipts + agreement controller.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
